data.enText: a part of a port where ships are repaired, or where goods are put onto or taken off them
a group of docks in a port and the buildings around them that are used for repairing ships, storing goods, etc.

data.chText: （供运货汽车或铁路货车装卸货物的）月台
data.enText: a raised platform for loading vehicles or trains
the part of a court where the person who has been accused of a crime stands or sits during a trial
He's been in the dock (= on trial for a crime) several times already.

data.chText: 酸模（北欧阔叶野草，用以揉擦被荨麻刺伤的皮肤，可止痛）
data.enText: a wild plant of northern Europe with large thick leaves that can be rubbed on skin that has been stung by nettles to make it less painful

data.chText: （使船）进港，停靠码头，进入船坞
data.enText: if a ship docks or you dock a ship, it sails into a harbour and stays there

data.chText: 渡船预计在6点停靠码头。
data.enText: The ferry is expected to dock at 6.

data.chText: （使宇宙飞船在外层空间）对接
data.enText: if two spacecraft dock , or are docked , they are joined together in space

data.chText: 明年将有一个技术舱与航天站对接。
data.enText: Next year, a technology module will be docked on the space station.
to take away part of sb's wages, etc.

data.chText: 如果你迟到了，就要扣你的工资。
data.enText: If you're late, your wages will be docked.

data.chText: 本周他们扣掉了我15%的工资。
data.enText: They've docked 15% off my pay for this week.

data.chText: 入坞（将电脑连接到扩展坞）
data.enText: to connect a computer to a docking station
to cut an animal's tail short

word_means: 进港，停靠码头，进入船坞

means: (供运货汽车或铁路货车装卸货物的)月台

ex.enText: He drove me to the wharf.

ex.chText: 他们正在码头上等候他们的父母。
ex.enText: They were waiting for their parents on the wharf.
The freighter slowly drew out from the wharf.

synonyms.bx: 指供船只停泊、乘客上下船或装卸货物的码头。

ex.chText: 我们在港口附近找了个位置下锚。
ex.enText: We took up a berth near the harbour.
The ship was staying at Berth 4.

ex.chText: 一艘轮船在码头锚地停泊。
ex.enText: A steamship was moored to its berth at the pier.

synonyms.bx: 指港口或码头附近供船只锚泊一段时间的水域。

ex.enText: The dock/wharf goes far out into the lake.

ex.chText: 他上了船，把船撑离了码头。
ex.enText: He boarded the boat and shoved off from the dock/wharf.
The liner was in dock for major repairs.

synonyms.bx: 作“码头”解时，与 wharf 同义，可换用；但作“船坞”解时，则不可换用，因 wharf 没有修理船只的功能。

ex.chText: 我们已建成一个凸式码头供远洋货轮停靠之用。
ex.enText: We have completed a pier to accommodate oceangoing freighters.
The big ship lies alongside the pier.

ex.chText: 新码头上有咖啡馆和饭馆。
ex.enText: The new pier has cafes and restaurants.

synonyms.bx: 指伸入河、湖、海中的突堤码头，可供乘客上下船、装卸货物或人们散步之用。

tr: a short or shortened tail of certain animals
the solid bony part of the tail of an animal as distinguished from the hair
landing in a harbor next to a pier where ships are loaded and unloaded or repaired
may have gates to let water in or out
example: the ship arrived at the dock more than a day late

tr: an enclosure in a court of law where the defendant sits during the trial
a platform where trucks or trains can be loaded or unloaded
a platform built out from the shore into the water and supported by piles
provides access to ships and boats
any of certain coarse weedy plants with long taproots, sometimes used as table greens or in folk medicine
remove or shorten the tail of an animal
deprive someone of benefits, as a penalty

value.def: A dock is an enclosed area in a harbour where ships go to be loaded, unloaded, and repaired.

example.ex: She headed for the docks, thinking that Ricardo might be hiding in one of the boats...
example.tran: 她走向码头，想着里卡多可能正藏在其中一条船上。

example.ex: What other ships are in dock here?
example.tran: 这儿的码头还有其他什么船只？

value.def: When a ship docks or is docked, it is brought into a dock.

example.ex: The vessel docked at Liverpool in April 1811...
example.tran: 这艘轮船于 1811 年 4 月在利物浦靠岸。

example.ex: Russian commanders docked a huge aircraft carrier in a Russian port...
example.tran: 俄罗斯指挥官指挥一艘巨型航空母舰驶入一个俄罗斯港口。

example.ex: The aircraft carrier has been docked there since last month.
example.tran: 自上个月以来那艘航空母舰就一直停靠在那儿。

value.def: When one spacecraft docks or is docked with another, the two crafts join together in space.

example.ex: The space shuttle Atlantis is scheduled to dock with Russia's Mir space station...
example.tran: 亚特兰蒂斯号航天飞机计划与俄国和平号空间站对接。

example.ex: They have docked a robot module alongside the orbiting space station...
example.tran: 他们已经将一个自动操作舱与沿轨道运行的空间站并行对接上了。

example.ex: The shuttle will spend five days docked with Mir.
example.tran: 航天飞机将和和平号对接5天。

value.def: A dock is a platform for loading vehicles or trains.

example.ex: The truck left the loading dock with hoses still attached.
example.tran: 卡车驶离装货月台时塑料水龙带还连在上面。

value.tran: (供运货汽车或铁路货车装卸货物的)月台

value.def: A dock is a small structure at the edge of water where boats can tie up, especially one that is privately owned.

example.ex: He had a house there and a dock and a little aluminum boat.
example.tran: 他在那儿有一所房子、一个泊船的码头和一艘小铝船。

value.tran: (尤指私人拥有的)船只停泊区

value.def: In a law court, the dock is where the person accused of a crime stands or sits.

example.ex: What about the odd chance that you do put an innocent man in the dock?
example.tran: 若是你真的把一个无辜的人送上被告席了呢？

value.def: If you dock someone's wages or money, you take some of the money away. If you dock someone points in a contest, you take away some of the points that they have.

example.ex: He threatens to dock her fee...
example.tran: 他威胁要扣掉她的服务费。

example.ex: To dock points would be wrong.

value.tran: 扣除(工资);减掉(竞赛中选手的分数)

value.def: A dock is a plant with large leaves which grows wild in Britain, the United States, and some other northern countries. Dock leaves are supposed to heal nettle stings.
value.tran: 酸模(常见于英、美等北方国家，叶子可用于治疗荨麻刺伤)
